sales.2018 <- analysis.2018[which(complete.cases(analysis.2018)), ]

y <- sales.2018 %>% gather(key = "kerosene", value = "kerosene.users", c(8,9)) %>% 
  gather(key = "bank", value = "bank.users", c(8,9)) %>%
  gather(key = "home,ownership", value = "home.stats", c(8,9)) %>%
  gather(key = "automobile", value = "motor.stats", c(8,9)) %>%
  gather(key = "gender", value = "gender.stats", c(8,9)) %>% 
  gather(key = "income", value = "income.stats", c(8:10)) %>% 
  gather(key = "stima", value = "stima.users", c(8,9))
set.seed(4321)
index <- sample(1:nrow(analysis.2019), 0.8*nrow(analysis.2019))

train <- analysis.2019[index, ]
test <- analysis.2019[-index, ]

fit1 <- lm(Number.of.units.sold~., data = train)
s1 <- summary(fit1)

fit2 <- lm(Number.of.units.sold~Month+Revenue+KEROSENE.YES+KEROSENE.YES+Bank.account.YES+Bank.account.NO+Stima.YES+Class, data = train)

s2 <- summary(fit2)

fit3 <- lm(Number.of.units.sold~Revenue+KEROSENE.NO+KEROSENE.YES+Bank.account.NO+Bank.account.NO+Does.the.client.Rent+Does.the.client.own.their.home+own.a.motorcycle.or.other.motorized.vehicle..NO+own.a.motorcycle.or.other.motorized.vehicle..YES+Gender.Female+Gender.Male+income.above.30.000+income.between.10.000.and.30.000+income.less.than.10.000+Stima.NO+Stima.YES+Class, data = train)


fit4 <- lm(Number.of.units.sold~Revenue+KEROSENE.NO+KEROSENE.YES+Bank.account.NO+Bank.account.NO+Does.the.client.Rent+Does.the.client.own.their.home+own.a.motorcycle.or.other.motorized.vehicle..NO+own.a.motorcycle.or.other.motorized.vehicle..YES+Gender.Female+Gender.Male+income.above.30.000+income.between.10.000.and.30.000+income.less.than.10.000+Stima.NO+Stima.YES+Class+Month, data = train)

fit5 <- lm(Number.of.units.sold~Month+Revenue+KEROSENE.YES+Bank.account.NO+income.less.than.10.000+Class+Stima.YES, data = train)
s5 <- summary(fit5)

pred <- predict(fit5, test)
act_pred <- data.frame(cbind(actuals = test$Number.of.units.sold, predicted = pred))
corretaion_accuracy <- cor(act_pred)
min_max_accuracy <- mean(apply(act_pred, 1, min)/apply(act_pred, 1, max))

normalize <- function(x){
  return((x-min(x))/(max(x)-min(x)))
}

ggplot(analysis.2019, aes(normalize(Revenue), normalize(Number.of.units.sold), col = Product.Name))+geom_point()

ggplot(analysis.2019, aes(normalize(Revenue), normalize(Number.of.units.sold)))+geom_point()+facet_wrap(~Product.Name)

ggplot(analysis.2019, aes(normalize(Revenue), normalize(Number.of.units.sold), col = Product.Name))+geom_line()

ggplot(analysis.2019, aes(normalize(KEROSENE.YES), normalize(Number.of.units.sold), col = Product.Name))+geom_point()
